metadata.name: Clerestory #210
metadata.description:
Windows welcome daylight, admit fresh air, and offer a view into the outside world. They rarely shatter, always confess the passage of time, and sometimes allow others a chance to look in.

What would the space you're in feel like if it had no windows?

'Clerestory' is an abstract exploration of stained glass windows, drafting shattered sketches for ten potential locations from various perspectives and moments in time. 

Made with WebGL, p5.js, and <3 | CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Pigments #142
metadata.description:
â€œPigmentsâ€ is a generative art project that explores the beauty of optical color blending and the power of noise. 

At the heart of this work is a random composition of rectangles that are made up of dots. These pigments are arranged in multiple layers, each layer using a different color from one of the carefully curated color palettes. Each palette consists of three to five colors. 

As the pigments are shifted by random noise, new hues and patterns emerge, creating a lovely display of color and movement.

In live mode:
- Press [1]-[5] to change the resolution.
- Press [s] to save a png file at the current resolution.

This is my first generative art project. Created with p5js.

________

Looks best on high-resolution screens and viewed in live mode. When displayed on a low-resolution screen, an unintended moirÃ© pattern may appear.

metadata.name: Isomorphic Realities #31
metadata.description:
I'm here and there at the same time.

Inspired by isomorphism, where a form can be transformed to another form by inverse mapping,this piece explores various transformations of the circle through mathematical equations and inversive geometry to create abstract forms.

The visuals created by the algorithm makes me think of alternative realities where abstract forms can transform into each other, that is why i named it 'Isomorphic Realities'.

Each minted piece is a generator where you can explore the sub-realities (inverted forms of the main form). Pressing 'i' will generate a new iteration based on the minted piece. Iteration number can be seen through the console.

There are two tiers in this Dutch Auction; minters from top tier will be eligible to a free airdrop of their preferred iteration minted on objktcom and transferred to their wallet. Please see my twitter for airdrop details. By doing this i aim to give some curation to minters within randomness.

Controls:

Press 'i' to generate new iterations based on the main iteration
Press 1-4 to export PNG between 1000px t0 4000px
Hold SHIFT and Press 1-4 to export PNG of the iteration 1000px to 4000px
Press 'r' to reset view back to main iteration

Experimental Export Options:

Open Console either right click and Inspect or ctrl(cmd) + shift + c

To export main image in higher resolution type : exportPNG(resolution,fileName)

To export iterated image in higher resolution type: 

exportIteration(iterationNumber,resolution,filename)

where resolution is your desired resolution(6000,8000,10000)
where filename is your desired filename. It must be in apostrophe ie "export8K"
where iterationNumber is the number of iteration and can be seen on browser console ie 17

Example usage:

exportPNG(8000,"8kImage")
exportIteration(12,8000,"Iteration8k")

Created with p5.js
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com
